==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in 1805. Sense 2 first attested in 1925. {{suffix|abrade|ive}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/əˈbɹeɪ.sɪv/|/əˈbɹeɪ.zɪv/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Producing [[abrasion]]; rough enough to wear away the outer surface. {{defdate|First attested in 1805.}}
# Being rough and coarse in manner or disposition; causing irritation. {{defdate|First attested in 1925.}}
#: ''An '''abrasive''' person can grate on one's sensibilities.''
#: ''Despite her proper upbringing, we found her manners to be terribly '''abrasive'''.''

